commit.message: Use test-unit and CoreAssertions instead of deep copy from ruby core repository.

Replace "iff" with "whether"

iff means if and only if, but readers without that knowledge might
assume this to be a spelling mistake. To me, this seems like
exclusionary language that is unnecessary. Simply using "whether"
when describing return values should suffice.
